  <prompt>
    Extend `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` to accept `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatMessageAttachment&gt;? attachments = null` as an optional backward-compatible parameter. Per spec FR-15, callers passing `null` or empty list MUST observe identical behavior to today (no regression for the no-files path). This task adds only the signature change + null-safe handling; downstream tasks 111-114 add the Phase A/B/C fingerprint + classification logic.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat-routing layer + backward-compat API evolution.</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` signature accepts an optional `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatMessageAttachment&gt;? attachments` parameter. Call-site grep shows new signature accepted; existing tests pass without modification (null/empty list = today's behavior); a new unit test confirms null + empty + 1-file all dispatch successfully via the message-only path.
  </prompt>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-15 + design §1.2 WP2. `PlaybookDispatcher.cs:150` is the current single-message dispatch entry point. To enable Hybrid C file-aware classification (FR-17), the dispatcher must accept per-turn attachments. This is wave 5-A — the foundation for the Phase A fingerprint (task 111), Phase B vector match (task 112), Phase C reconciliation (task 113), and gpt-4o-mini decider (task 114). Backward-compat is binding: existing tests must pass unmodified.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcher.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatMessageAttachment.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcherTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15">Backward-compat: existing tests pass without modification; null/empty = today's behavior.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; expect minor delta only.</constraint>
