  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookDispatcher.cs:150` current `DispatchAsync` signature; understand the existing message-only path.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `ChatMessageAttachment.cs` to confirm the shape (filename, contentType, textContent, etc.).</step>
    <step order="3">Add `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatMessageAttachment&gt;? attachments = null` as a new parameter at the END of `DispatchAsync` (preserve binary compat for callers).</step>
    <step order="4">In the dispatcher body, ADD a guard at the top: if `attachments == null || attachments.Count == 0`, fall through to the existing message-only logic. (Phase A/B/C logic lands in tasks 111-114.)</step>
    <step order="5">Grep call sites of `DispatchAsync`. Confirm zero are broken by the new optional parameter; document call-site list.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs` (or whoever resolves attachments per-turn) to pass attachments where available; preserve null when absent.</step>
    <step order="7">Add a new unit test in `PlaybookDispatcherTests.cs` asserting: (a) null attachments dispatches identically to today; (b) empty list dispatches identically; (c) 1-attachment dispatches successfully (today via message-only path; tasks 111-114 will extend with file-aware logic).</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Existing tests must pass without modification; new test passes.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure BFF publish size; report delta vs Phase 4 baseline.</step>
    <step order="10">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 110 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 111.</step>
  </steps>

